value.title: Can Donald Trump Pass $2,000 Stimulus Checks by Executive Order?
value.excerpt: With a standalone bill that would allow $2,000 stimulus checks apparently dead in the Senate, could President Donald Trump sign an executive order that would allow the higher direct payments to reach Americans?

value.title: Joe Biden's Approach to Latin America Will Be Major Departure from Donald Trump
value.excerpt: Joe Biden believes, and he has for years, that conditions must be improved in Latin America if the United States wants to slow immigration. A less antagonistic U.S. approach is coming.

value.title: Trump's kids won't lose their 5th Amendment rights and be forced to testify against him if they're pardoned, experts say
value.excerpt: A presidential pardon isn't enough to mean that someone can't plead the Fifth Amendment and refuse to testify, according to criminal law experts.

value.title: One of Trump's 'biggest services to America' was exposing liberal media: Jeffrey Lord
value.excerpt: One of President Trump's top accomplishments came not on the domestic policy or foreign policy front, but in simply exposing left-wing media figures for their biases, columnist and political analyst Jeffrey Lord said Wednesday on "The Ingraham Angle."

value.title: Trump administration declassifying unconfirmed intel that indicates China offered bounties to attack Americans in Afghanistan, official says
value.excerpt: The Trump administration is declassifying intelligence, so far unconfirmed, that indicates China offered bounties to non-state actors to attack American soldiers in Afghanistan, according to a senior administration official.

value.title: Computer repairman: Twitter calling me hacker in Hunter Biden laptop case was 'death sentence'
value.excerpt: The computer repairman at the center of the Hunter Biden laptop story said Thursday that Twitter destroyed his business by labeling him a "hacker" and legal action was his only recourse.

value.title: Live politics updates: Trump to return to DC early, GOP senator says he's 'playing with fire' in contesting election
value.excerpt: Sasse said the effort by Trump and his allies to overturn Biden's win amounted to pointing a "loaded gun at the heart of legitimate self-government."

value.title: Trump returning to White House early from holiday vacation at Mar-a-Lago

value.title: Trump versus the truth: The most outrageous falsehoods of his presidency
value.excerpt: I have never seen a president in American history who has lied so continuously and so outrageously as Donald Trump, period,” presidential historian Michael Beschloss said.

value.title: Alec Baldwin should play himself in 'SNL' sketch about wife's heritage controversy: Trump Jr.
value.excerpt: Donald Trump Jr Wednesday suggested actor Alec Baldwin should play himself in a "Saturday Night Live" sketch about his wife Hilaria’s scandal over her heritage.

value.title: Biden campaign promises included decriminalizing HIV exposure
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has promised to "advance LGBTQ equality" by reversing decades-old criminalization of HIV exposure and transmission laws that have no "scientific basis" and contribute to stigmas.

value.title: Trump asks Supreme Court to void Wisconsin election results
value.excerpt: Trump’s attorneys filed a motion asking the Supreme Court to consider his case in an expedited manner.

value.title: Biden to issue executive order halting any Trump 'midnight regulations'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden will issue an executive order halting "midnight regulations" on day one of his presidency, incoming White House press secretary Jen Psaki said Wednesday.

value.title: Census Bureau to miss deadline, threatening Trump's attempt to exclude illegal migrants from census
value.excerpt: For the first time in four decades the Census Bureau will miss their deadline on reporting apportionment figures used to divvy up congressional seats.

value.title: Senate moves toward override of Trump's NDAA veto
value.excerpt: A final Senate vote on whether to override Trump’s veto is expected to take place by Saturday before Congress adjourns its current session.

value.title: Acosta's admission he'll go easier on Biden shows 'personal vendetta' against Trump: Kurtz
value.excerpt: Fox News media analyst Howard Kurtz told "America’s Newsroom" Wednesday that CNN White House correspondent Jim Acosta’s admission he will approach a Biden White House in less adversarial fashion shows he's brought a "personal vendetta" to his reporting on the Trump administration.

value.title: Biden to take swift action to roll back harmful 'midnight regulations' -transition team
value.excerpt: The Biden administration will take swift action when it assumes office on Jan. 20 to rollback harmful Trump administration policies that will not have taken effect by inauguration day, a spokeswoman for President-elect Joe Biden's transition team said on Wednesday.

value.title: Thomas L. Friedman column: Will Trump force principled conservatives to start their own party? I hope so.
value.excerpt: As the Trump presidency heads into the sunset, kicking and screaming, one of the most important questions that will shape American politics at the local, state and national levels is this: Can Donald Trump maintain his iron grip over the Republican Party when he is out of office?

value.title: President-elect Joe Biden and wife Jill to appear "Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve"
value.excerpt: Hosts and performers for the annual Times Square celebration, which will look different this year due to the pandemic, have also been announced.

value.title: Joe and Jill Biden to appear on Ryan Seacrest's 'New Year's Rockin' Eve'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden and his wife, Dr. Jill Biden, will join Ryan Seacrest on Thursday night's "Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve."

value.title: Trump is reportedly planning to host hundreds of guests at a lavish New Year's Eve bash at Mar-a-Lago as COVID-19 cases continue to soar
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has been busy preparing for a New Year's Eve gala as many areas of the country continue to report surges in coronavirus cases.

value.title: Trump calls for Georgia Gov. Brian Kemp, a fellow Republican, to resign
value.excerpt: The president’s demand stems from the governor’s refusal to embrace Trump’s baseless claims of widespread election fraud.

value.title: Pence's former top aide said that Trump is 'encouraging' violence on the day Congress votes to seal the 2020 presidential election results
value.excerpt: President Trump has promised his supporters there would be a "wild" rally in the capital on the day of Congress votes to approve the election result.

value.title: A congressional waiver is the biggest hurdle for Biden's defense pick
value.excerpt: The biggest obstacle to retired Army Gen. Lloyd Austin's nomination for secretary of defense is his retirement date from the military just four years ago -- too recent under American law and for the tastes of several members of Congress.
